                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.80/9–1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d482fn1">Repeated for information to London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-11T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 11, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. I feel impelled to say that I have been surprised by extent our relations in
                    this part of world have suffered as result of our stand on Suez restrictions,
                    and I apprehend we will be suffering from this for some time. It has caused, for
                    instance, a recrudescence of the Pal question which in Egypt had become
                    quiescent, and may have bearing on our ability to do things, particularly in
                    connection Anglo-Egypt negots. It has caused Arab revival of talk for closer
                    relations with Russia.</p>
                <p>I report this only because it is better to face facts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
